item.description:
Multi-address per type using existing DB columns.
- collection_address column → pickup addresses
- delivery_address column → delivery addresses

Each address object: { id, address, town_city, postcode, label, created_at }
Existing single-object data is auto-wrapped with id='legacy'.

GET ?type=pickup  → { type:'pickup',   addresses:[] }
GET ?type=delivery → { type:'delivery', addresses:[] }
GET (no type)      → { pickup_addresses:[], delivery_addresses:[] }

request.description:
Test: call create-link on a 24h order while delivery_request is still 'pending'.

Expected 400:
{
  success: false,
  message: 'Waiting for seller to approve or reject the 24-hour delivery request.',
  data: { delivery_request_status: 'pending', remaining_seconds: 3542 }
}

Simulates a failed payment webhook from Mamo.

Expected: order status stays 'pending_payment', no update.
{
  success: true,
  message: 'Status "failed" received, no action taken.'
}

Call verify again on an already-paid order.

Expected idempotent response:
{
  success: true,
  message: 'Payment already confirmed.'
}

Try to create a payment link for an already-paid order.

Expected 400:
{
  success: false,
  message: 'This order is already paid.'
}

